  "response_text": "Let  \n\\[\nS=\\sum_{k=1}^{1009}\\frac{k(k+2)}{(2k+1)(2k+3)}.\n\\]\n\nWe first rewrite each term:\n\\[\nk(k+2)=\\frac{(2k+1)(2k+3)-3}{4},\n\\]\nsince\n\\[\n(2k+1)(2k+3)=4k^2+8k+3\n\\]\nand\n\\[\n4k(k+2)=4k^2+8k.\n\\]\nSo\n\\[\n\\frac{k(k+2)}{(2k+1)(2k+3)}\n=\\frac14-\\frac{3}{4(2k+1)(2k+3)}.\n\\]\n\nNow use partial fractions:\n\\[\n\\frac{1}{(2k+1)(2k+3)}\n=\\frac12\\left(\\frac1{2k+1}-\\frac1{2k+3}\\right).\n\\]\nHence\n\\[\nS=\\sum_{k=1}^{1009}\\left(\\frac14-\\frac{3}{8}\\left(\\frac1{2k+1}-\\frac1{2k+3}\\right)\\right).\n\\]\n\nThis telescopes:\n\\[\n\\sum_{k=1}^{1009}\\left(\\frac1{2k+1}-\\frac1{2k+3}\\right)\n=\\frac13-\\frac1{2021}.\n\\]\nTherefore\n\\[\nS=\\frac{1009}{4}-\\frac{3}{8}\\left(\\frac13-\\frac1{2021}\\right).\n\\]\nCompute:\n\\[\n\\frac{3}{8}\\cdot\\frac13=\\frac18,\\qquad\n\\frac{3}{8}\\cdot\\frac1{2021}=\\frac{3}{16168}.\n\\]\nSo\n\\[\nS=\\frac{1009}{4}-\\frac18+\\frac{3}{16168}\n=\\frac{2018}{8}-\\frac18+\\frac{3}{16168}\n=\\frac{2017}{8}+\\frac{3}{16168}.\n\\]\nPutting over a common denominator \\(16168\\):\n\\[\n\\frac{2017}{8}=\\frac{2017\\cdot 2021}{16168}=\\frac{4077357}{16168},\n\\]\nso\n\\[\nS=\\frac{4077357+3}{16168}=\\frac{4077360}{16168}=\\frac{1019340}{4042}=\\frac{509670}{2021}.\n\\]\n\nFinal answer: \\(\\boxed{\\frac{509670}{2021}}\\)",
